# Project Structure

Usertour is an open-source user onboarding platform that allows you to create in-app product tours, checklists, and surveys. It's built as a monorepo with a modern architecture.

## Apps Directory
- [apps/server](mdc:apps/server) - Backend API built with NestJS, handling authentication, user management, project management, and analytics
- [apps/web](mdc:apps/web) - Frontend web application built with React, providing the main user interface for creating and managing tours
- [apps/sdk](mdc:apps/sdk) - Usertour.js SDK for integrating tours into client applications

## Packages Directory
- [packages/components](mdc:packages/components) - Shared UI components library with Radix UI primitives and custom components
- [packages/radix](mdc:packages/radix) - Radix UI primitive components and utilities
- [packages/shared](mdc:packages/shared) - Shared utilities, types, hooks, and internationalization resources

## Configuration Files
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Root package configuration and workspace setup
- [turbo.json](mdc:turbo.json) - Turborepo configuration for monorepo build optimization
- [biome.json](mdc:biome.json) - Code formatting and linting configuration
- [docker-compose.yml](mdc:docker-compose.yml) - Docker deployment configuration
- [pnpm-workspace.yaml](mdc:pnpm-workspace.yaml) - PNPM workspace configuration

## Key Features Supported
- Multi-environment support (Production, Staging)
- Version control and change tracking
- Customizable themes and branding
- Advanced user targeting and segmentation
- Analytics and performance metrics
- Multi-page application support
- Framework-agnostic SDK integration

